<subSubSection id="C34C72A24B1CFF9214F9D236FEF0FB47" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1CFF9214F9D236FEF0FB47" blockId="7.[136,1452,878,1193]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9214F9D236FF5DFC66" box="[136,189,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Note</emphasis>
:According to the protologue (see also Boissier 1839-1845, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF92170FD237FB95FC66" author="Gonzalez Bueno, A." box="[894,1141,878,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" pagination="5 - 21" refId="ref9515" refString="Gonzalez Bueno, A. (2010) El viaje botanico de Pierre Edmond Boissier por el sur de Espana (1837). Acta Botanica Malacitana 35: 5 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 35 i 0.2872" type="journal article" year="2010">González Bueno 2010</bibRefCitation>
) the 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B1CFF9210DBD237FAF1FC66" box="[1194,1297,878,904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">lectotype</typeStatus>
was collected in 
<quantity id="4CAE8CCC4B1CFF9214D6D2CBFEE2FC42" box="[167,258,914,940]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66598" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" unit="in" value="1837.0">1837 in</quantity>
: “Sierra Bermeja, Estepona” (Boissier 1839-1845(vol. 2): 585) or “Sierra de la Nieve” [according to the protologue: perhaps in Yunquera (Boissier 1839-1845(vol. 2): 585)], on 15 May [according to Boissier (1839-1845(vol. 1): 51, 55) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF921530D283FD93FC1A" author="Gonzalez Bueno, A." box="[321,627,986,1013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" pagination="5 - 21" refId="ref9515" refString="Gonzalez Bueno, A. (2010) El viaje botanico de Pierre Edmond Boissier por el sur de Espana (1837). Acta Botanica Malacitana 35: 5 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 35 i 0.2872" type="journal article" year="2010">González Bueno (2010: 9)</bibRefCitation>
for the material collected in Sierra Bermeja, Estepona] and September [according to the protologue for the material collected in “Sierra de la Nieve” (Yunquera?), see also Boissier (1839- 1845(vol. 1): 155) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF9215EAD57BFD28FBD2" author="Gonzalez Bueno, A." box="[411,712,1058,1085]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" pagination="5 - 21" refId="ref9515" refString="Gonzalez Bueno, A. (2010) El viaje botanico de Pierre Edmond Boissier por el sur de Espana (1837). Acta Botanica Malacitana 35: 5 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 35 i 0.2872" type="journal article" year="2010">González Bueno (2010: 9</bibRefCitation>
, 13)]. This material was collected by E. Boissier [according to the protologue and Boissier (1839-1845, 1: 41, 51, 155) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF92173BD51FFBBFFB8F" author="Gonzalez Bueno, A." box="[842,1119,1094,1121]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" pagination="5 - 21" refId="ref9515" refString="Gonzalez Bueno, A. (2010) El viaje botanico de Pierre Edmond Boissier por el sur de Espana (1837). Acta Botanica Malacitana 35: 5 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 35 i 0.2872" type="journal article" year="2010">González Bueno (2010)</bibRefCitation>
], together with David Ravey and Antonio (in the collection on 15 May), and David Ravey, Pablo Prolongo &amp; F. Haenseler (in the collection on September).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
